complexity-critique
===================

Upstream chain
--------------

This skill is adapted from a chain of MIT-licensed upstream projects:

1. joshuadavidthomas `agent-skills/skills/reducing-entropy` — the
   earliest upstream.
   https://github.com/joshuadavidthomas/agent-skills/tree/main/skills/reducing-entropy
   License: MIT. Copyright (c) joshuadavidthomas. Contributes the
   philosophical mindset selection (data-over-abstractions,
   design-is-taking-apart, expensive-to-add-later, simplicity-vs-easy)
   and the deletion-first three-question gate concept.

2. softaworks `agent-toolkit/skills/reducing-entropy` — direct
   upstream (fork of #1).
   https://github.com/softaworks/agent-toolkit/tree/main/skills/reducing-entropy
   License: MIT. Carries forward the original skill structure with
   minor packaging adjustments. The kouko fork-of-fork lineage flows
   from this distribution.

3. kouko monkey-skills — this distribution, renamed to
   `complexity-critique`.
   https://github.com/kouko/monkey-skills
   Path: dev-workflow/skills/complexity-critique/
   License: MIT. Copyright (c) 2026 kouko.

Modifications in this distribution (kouko)
------------------------------------------

See dev-workflow/CHANGELOG.md for the full per-version modification
list. High-level summary (v1.5.0):

- Renamed `reducing-entropy` → `complexity-critique` for clearer
  trigger semantics (entropy is jargon; complexity-critique parallels
  the existing `proposal-critique` skill in dev-workflow)
- Mindset library extracted to `domain-teams:code-team/standards/`
  as 4 separate standards (`mindset-data-over-abstractions.md`,
  `mindset-design-is-taking-apart.md`,
  `mindset-expensive-to-add-later.md`,
  `mindset-simplicity-vs-easy.md`) with primary-source citations
  rewritten against the underlying books / talks / papers
  (Perlis 1982, Hickey 2011/2012, Moseley & Marks 2006, Ousterhout
  2018, Brooks 1986, Willison/Plant/Kaplan-Moss 2021)
- Cross-plugin delegation: this skill references the mindsets via
  `domain-teams:code-team` paths, not by content duplication, per
  monkey-skills CLAUDE.md §Cross-Plugin Delegation Contract
- Restructured SKILL.md to mirror dev-workflow conventions
  (frontmatter description with negative triggers, multilingual
  Triggers, Composes With section, Worked Examples, When To Apply
  with Not-triggers)
- Three-question gate retained but tightened: explicit verdict
  vocabulary (PROCEED / PROCEED-WITH-CAVEAT / RESHAPE / REJECT)
  parallel to `proposal-critique`'s KEEP / KEEP-WITH-CAVEAT / DEFER /
  DROP
- Scope clarified to *changes to existing codebase*; greenfield
  design and post-implementation review explicitly out of scope
  (delegated to `superpowers:brainstorming` and Anthropic `simplify`
  respectively)
- **Restored** (v1.5.0 fidelity follow-up) the "load at least one
  mindset before proceeding" hard precondition that an earlier
  draft of this distribution had removed. The original author
  designed this as a deliberate gate — the three questions on their
  own are mechanical (count lines, list obsolete) and the mindset
  is what gives them design judgment. The §Before You Begin
  preamble enforces it; an advisory-mode fallback is provided when
  `domain-teams:code-team` is not installed (mindsets recited inline
  and user nominates a plain-language anchor)
- Added Worked Examples section (form-validation feature add;
  type-safety refactor) demonstrating the verdict vocabulary
- Removed the upstream `references/` directory (mindsets moved to
  domain-teams:code-team) and `adding-reference-mindsets.md`
  meta-skill (replaced by skill-team conventions for adding new
  standards)

